        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 515 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Milford, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pontiac, Fenton, Milford, Holly, Ortonville, Clarkston, West
Bloomfield, Lake Fenton, Auburn Hills, Wixom, Walled Lake, Wolverine
Lake, Keego Harbor, Sylvan Lake, Lake Angelus, Waterford, Orchard
Lake, Davisburg, Holly State Recreation Area, and Commerce.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
